    </refmeta>

    <refnamediv>
      <refname>ss-display</refname>

      <refpurpose>display message in the dashboard</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>

    <refsynopsisdiv>
      <cmdsynopsis>
        <command>ss-display</command>

        <arg><option>-v</option>, <option>--verbose</option></arg>

        <arg><option>-h</option>, <option>--help</option></arg>

        <arg choice="req" rep="norepeat"><replaceable>message</replaceable></arg>
      </cmdsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>

    <refsection>
      <title>Description</title>

      <para>The <command>ss-display</command> command is a convenience command
      to display a message in the dashboard. It is useful to make the deployment
      more lively, showing for example at which step the deployment scripts are
      at.</para>
    </refsection>

    <refsection>
      <title>Options</title>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><option>-v</option>, <option>--verbose</option></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>verbose level. Add more to get more details.</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><option>-h</option>, <option>--help</option></term>

          <listitem>
            <para>show this help message and exit</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </refsection>
  </refentry>

